channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Confessions of a 1980s flight attendant
item.description: Ann Hood, a best-selling author, has recounted her adventures working as cabin crew on TWA flights in the 1980s in a book detailing the highs and lows of life during the early jet age.

item.title: Wildfire north of Los Angeles spreads as authorities issue evacuation orders
item.description: Wildfire spread thousands of acres close to a major highway, officials say.

item.title: The Gilgo Beach Serial Killings
item.description: The bound bodies of four women are found along a desolate stretch of beach. Disturbing new details about the architect police say is a serial killer. "48 Hours" correspondent Erin Moriarty reports.

item.title: June 13, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The US-backed Gaza ceasefire proposal doesn't meet Hamas' demands for an end to the war, a senior official has told CNN. Osama Hamdan also said that "no one has an idea" how many of the hostages held in the enclave are alive.

item.title: Israel-Gaza live updates: IDF to begin daily 'tactical pause' along Gaza aid route
item.description: More than seven months after Hamas terrorists invaded Israel on Oct. 7, the Israeli military continues its bombardment of the neighboring Gaza Strip.

item.description: The twists and turns in the search for three missing women would challenge their families and two investigators, brought together by chance, who embarked on the most complex cat-and-mouse game of their careers.

item.title: Biden and Zelensky lay out new US support for Ukraine
item.description: US President Joe Biden and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signed a new security agreement Thursday as world leaders gathered for the G7 summit in Italy.

item.title: Multiple people shot at splash pad park, suspect dead: Police
item.description: Police said they have a suspect contained after they allegedly opened fire at a Rochester Hills, Michigan splash pad that was filled with visitors.
